# 1. What is Jinja2?

## Definition

Jinja2 is the default template engine used by Flask.

It allows Python data to be displayed inside HTML pages.

Instead of showing static HTML, Jinja2 creates **dynamic webpages**.

---

## Real-Time Example

Suppose the employee name is:

```text
Rahul
```

Without Jinja2

```html
<h2>Employee Name</h2>
```

Output

```text
Employee Name
```

With Jinja2

```html
<h2>{{ name }}</h2>
```

Output

```text
Rahul
```

---

## Answer

Jinja2 is a template engine that allows Flask to send Python variables to HTML.

---

