# 4. Passing Data from Flask

Example

```python
return render_template(
    "result.html",
    name=name
)
```

Here,

Python sends the variable

```text
name
```

to

```text
result.html
```

---

## Answer

`render_template()` sends variables from Flask to HTML.

---

# 5. Create result.html

Inside

```text
templates
```

Create

```text
result.html
```

---

Write

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>

<html>

<head>

<title>Employee Details</title>

</head>

<body>

<h1>Employee Information</h1>

<h2>Employee Name : {{ name }}</h2>

</body>

</html>
```

---

## Answer

`{{ name }}` displays the value received from Flask.

---

# 6. Update app.py

```python
from flask import Flask, render_template, request

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/", methods=["GET","POST"])
def home():

    if request.method == "POST":

        name = request.form["name"]

        return render_template(
            "result.html",
            name=name
        )

    return render_template("index.html")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run(debug=True)
```

---

# Output

User enters

```text
Rahul
```

Browser displays

```text
Employee Information

Employee Name : Rahul
```

---

## Answer

Flask passes the value of **name** to HTML using `render_template()`.

